In view of these changes it is said that Res judicata, like Litis contestatio, while it retained its positive functione, lost its negative functions. But while it still generated an exceptio rei judicatae it seems difficult to say that it ceased to have a negative or consump- tive operation: though this was attenuated, and made more rig-orously subsidiary to the positive operation 3 and was henceforth left entirely to the discretiori of the praetor.
